        "body": "## Summary\r\nFixes the hover effect layering issue on feature cards where the hover highlight was rendering on top of the card content instead of behind it.\r\n## Problem\r\nThe spotlight/hover effect on the feature cards (AI Transcription, Multi-Platform, Quality Score, Analytics, 10x Speed) was overlapping the icon, title, and description — making the content visually obstructed on hover.\r\n## Changes Made\r\n\r\ncard-hover-effect.tsx — Updated the HoverEffect wrapper to render the spotlight effect behind the card content using proper z-index layering\r\nPremiumFeatures.tsx — Cleaned up unused logic and resolved TypeScript key warnings\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\nThe hover overlay element had a higher z-index than the card content, causing it to stack on top instead of behind.\r\n## Fix\r\n\r\nSet hover overlay to z-index: 0\r\nSet card content (icon, title, description) to position: relative and z-index: 1\r\n\r\n",
