        "body": "**Bug: Card hover effect renders on top of content instead of behind it**\n\n**Description**\nThe hover effect/highlight on the feature cards is appearing above the card content (icon, title, description) instead of rendering in the background layer. This causes the hover state to visually overlap or obscure the card's content.\n\n**Steps to Reproduce**\n1. Navigate to the features section\n2. Hover over any feature card (e.g., Analytics, 10x Speed, etc.)\n3. Observe the hover highlight effect\n\n**Expected Behavior**\nThe hover effect should render behind the card content — acting as a background highlight — so the icon, title, and description remain fully visible and unobstructed.\n\n**Actual Behavior**\nThe hover effect appears on top of (above) the card content, overlapping the text and icon.\n\n**Root Cause (suspected)**\nThe hover overlay element likely has a `z-index` higher than the card content, or the card content is missing a `position` and `z-index` to stack above the overlay.\n\n**Suggested Fix**\n- Set the hover overlay to `z-index: 0` (or a low value)\n- Ensure card content (icon, title, description) has `position: relative` and `z-index: 1`\n\n**Environment**\n- Component: Feature Cards Grid\n- Affected cards: All (AI Transcription, Multi-Platform, Quality Score, Analytics, 10x Speed)\n\n**Screenshot**\n- Before\n\n<img width=\"1376\" height=\"596\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b3286c35-997f-44e9-b999-9b205897fa5b\" />\n\n- After\n\n<img width=\"1366\" height=\"560\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/471eda78-6249-4ca0-84a0-d2d7c809675f\" />",
