        "body": "The links in the website footer (Links section) are not displaying any hover effect, which negatively impacts the user interface experience and visual feedback.\n\n### Current Behavior\n\n- Footer links under the \"Links\" section (About Us, Contact Us, Our Team, Get Involved, Privacy Policy, CloudCV Website) do not show any visual change on hover\n- No indication to users that the elements are clickable/interactive\n- Inconsistent with standard web UI patterns\n- The links remain in their default gray color (#A0A0A0 approximately) without any visual feedback\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\n- Footer links should display a hover effect (e.g., color change, underline, opacity change)\n- Clear visual feedback when users move their cursor over the links\n- Improved user experience with better interactivity cues\n\n### **Steps to Reproduce**\n\n1. Navigate to any page on the website\n2. Scroll down to the footer section\n3. Hover your cursor over any footer links\n4. Observe that there is no visual change or hover effect\n\n### **Suggested Solution**\nAdd CSS hover states to footer links. Possible implementations:\n\n<img width=\"1512\" height=\"982\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ecea4a36-b64f-4f3c-9e0e-28d6ef4c41a0\" />\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b1aefdd0-67ac-4180-8686-b5da87a799db\n",
